00056   class Spec {
00057   protected:
00059     const int* data;
00061     int l, u;
00062   public:
00064     bool valid(void) const {
00065       return data != NULL;
00066     }
00068     int capacity(void) const {
00069       return data[0];
00070     }
00072     int items(void) const {
00073       return data[1];
00074     }
00076     int size(int i) const {
00077       return data[i+2];
00078     }
00079   protected:
00081     static const int* find(const char* s) {
00082       for (int i=0; name[i] != NULL; i++)
00083         if (!strcmp(s,name[i]))
00084           return bpp[i];
00085       return NULL;
00086     }
00088     int clower(void) const {
00089       /*
00090        * The lower bound is due to: S. Martello, P. Toth. Lower bounds
00091        * and reduction procedures for the bin packing problem.
00092        * Discrete and applied mathematics, 28(1):59-70, 1990.
00093        */
00094       const int c = capacity(), n = items();
00095       int l = 0;
00096 
00097       // Items in N1 are from 0 ... n1 - 1
00098       int n1 = 0;
00099       // Items in N2 are from n1 ... n12 - 1, we count elements in N1 and N2
00100       int n12 = 0;
00101       // Items in N3 are from n12 ... n3 - 1
00102       int n3 = 0;
00103       // Free space in N2
00104       int f2 = 0;
00105       // Total size of items in N3
00106       int s3 = 0;
00107 
00108       // Initialize n12 and f2
00109       for (; (n12 < n) && (size(n12) > c/2); n12++)
00110         f2 += c - size(n12);
00111 
00112       // Initialize n3 and s3
00113       for (n3 = n12; n3 < n; n3++)
00114         s3 += size(n3);
00115 
00116       // Compute lower bounds
00117       for (int k=0; k<=c/2; k++) {
00118         // Make N1 larger by adding elements and N2 smaller
00119         for (; (n1 < n) && (size(n1) > c-k); n1++)
00120           f2 -= c - size(n1);
00121         assert(n1 <= n12);
00122         // Make N3 smaller by removing elements
00123         for (; (size(n3-1) < k) && (n3 > n12); n3--)
00124           s3 -= size(n3-1);
00125         // Overspill
00126         int o = (s3 > f2) ? ((s3 - f2 + c - 1) / c) : 0;
00127         l = std::max(l, n12 + o);
00128       }
00129       return l;
00130     }
00132     int cupper(void) const {
00133       // Use a naive greedy algorithm
00134       const int c = capacity(), n = items();
00135 
00136       int* f = new int[n];
00137       for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00138         f[i] = c;
00139 
00140       int u=0;
00141       for (int i=0; i<n; i++) {
00142         int j=0;
00143         // Skip bins with insufficient free space
00144         while (f[j] < size(i))
00145           j++;
00146         if (j > u) {
00147           // A new bin is needed
00148           u = j; f[u] -= size(i);
00149         } else {
00150           // The slack of the best-fit bin
00151           int b = j++;
00152           int s = f[b] - size(i);
00153           while (j <= u) {
00154             if ((f[j] >= size(i)) && (f[j] - size(i) < s)) {
00155               b = j; s = f[b] - size(i);
00156             }
00157             j++;
00158           }
00159           f[b] -= size(i);
00160         }
00161       }
00162       delete [] f;
00163       return u+1;
00164     }
00165   public:
00167     Spec(const char* s) : data(find(s)), l(0), u(0) {
00168       if (valid()) {
00169         l = clower(); u = cupper();
00170       }
00171     }
00173     int total(void) const {
00174       int t=0;
00175       for (int i=0; i<items(); i++)
00176         t += size(i);
00177       return t;
00178     }
00180     int lower(void) const {
00181       return l;
00182     }
00184     int upper(void) const {
00185       return u;
00186     }
00187   };
00188 
00189 }

00202 class CDBF : public Brancher {
00203 protected:
00205   ViewArray<Int::IntView> load;
00207   ViewArray<Int::IntView> bin;
00209   IntSharedArray size;
00211   mutable int item;
00213   class Choice : public Gecode::Choice {
00214   public:
00216     int item;
00218     int* same;
00220     int n_same;
00224     Choice(const Brancher& b, unsigned int a, int i, int* s, int n_s)
00225       : Gecode::Choice(b,a), item(i),
00226         same(heap.alloc<int>(n_s)), n_same(n_s) {
00227       for (int k=n_same; k--; )
00228         same[k] = s[k];
00229     }
00231     virtual size_t size(void) const {
00232       return sizeof(Choice) + sizeof(int) * n_same;
00233     }
00235     virtual void archive(Archive& e) const {
00236       Gecode::Choice::archive(e);
00237       e << alternatives() << item << n_same;
00238       for (int i=n_same; i--;)
00239         e << same[i];
00240     }
00242     virtual ~Choice(void) {
00243       heap.free<int>(same,n_same);
00244     }
00245   };
00246 
00247 public:
00249   CDBF(Home home, ViewArray<Int::IntView>& l, ViewArray<Int::IntView>& b,
00250        IntSharedArray& s)
00251     : Brancher(home), load(l), bin(b), size(s), item(0) {
00252     home.notice(*this,AP_DISPOSE);
00253   }
00255   static void post(Home home, ViewArray<Int::IntView>& l,
00256                    ViewArray<Int::IntView>& b,
00257                    IntSharedArray& s) {
00258     (void) new (home) CDBF(home, l, b, s);
00259   }
00261   CDBF(Space& home, bool share, CDBF& cdbf)
00262     : Brancher(home, share, cdbf), item(cdbf.item) {
00263     load.update(home, share, cdbf.load);
00264     bin.update(home, share, cdbf.bin);
00265     size.update(home, share, cdbf.size);
00266   }
00268   virtual Actor* copy(Space& home, bool share) {
00269     return new (home) CDBF(home, share, *this);
00270   }
00272   virtual size_t dispose(Space& home) {
00273     home.ignore(*this,AP_DISPOSE);
00274     size.~IntSharedArray();
00275     return sizeof(*this);
00276   }
00278   virtual bool status(const Space&) const {
00279     for (int i = item; i < bin.size(); i++)
00280       if (!bin[i].assigned()) {
00281         item = i; return true;
00282       }
00283     return false;
00284   }
00286   virtual Gecode::Choice* choice(Space& home) {
00287     assert(!bin[item].assigned());
00288 
00289     int n = bin.size(), m = load.size();
00290 
00291     Region region(home);
00292 
00293     // Free space in bins
00294     int* free = region.alloc<int>(m);
00295 
00296     for (int j=m; j--; )
00297       free[j] = load[j].max();
00298     for (int i=n; i--; )
00299       if (bin[i].assigned())
00300         free[bin[i].val()] -= size[i];
00301 
00302     // Equivalent bins with same free space
00303     int* same = region.alloc<int>(m+1);
00304     unsigned int n_same = 0;
00305     unsigned int n_possible = 0;
00306 
00307     // Initialize such that failure is guaranteed (pack into bin -1)
00308     same[n_same++] = -1;
00309 
00310     // Find a best-fit bin for item
00311     int slack = INT_MAX;
00312     for (Int::ViewValues<Int::IntView> j(bin[item]); j(); ++j)
00313       if (size[item] <= free[j.val()]) {
00314         // Item still can fit into the bin
00315         n_possible++;
00316         if (free[j.val()] - size[item] < slack) {
00317           // A new, better fit
00318           slack = free[j.val()] - size[item];
00319           same[0] = j.val(); n_same = 1;
00320         } else if (free[j.val()] - size[item] == slack) {
00321           // An equivalent bin, remember it
00322           same[n_same++] = j.val();
00323         }
00324       }
00325     /*
00326      * Domination rules:
00327      *  - if the item fits the bin exactly, just assign
00328      *  - if all possible bins are equivalent, just assign
00329      *
00330      * Also catches failure: if no possible bin was found, commit
00331      * the item into bin -1.
00332      */
00333     if ((slack == 0) || (n_same == n_possible) || (slack == INT_MAX))
00334       return new Choice(*this, 1, item, same, 1);
00335     else
00336       return new Choice(*this, 2, item, same, n_same);
00337   }
00339   virtual const Gecode::Choice* choice(const Space& home, Archive& e) {
00340     int alt, item, n_same;
00341     e >> alt >> item >> n_same;
00342     Region re(home);
00343     int* same = re.alloc<int>(n_same);
00344     for (int i=n_same; i--;) e >> same[i];
00345     return new Choice(*this, alt, item, same, n_same);
00346   }
00348   virtual ExecStatus commit(Space& home, const Gecode::Choice& _c,
00349                             unsigned int a) {
00350     const Choice& c = static_cast<const Choice&>(_c);
00351     // This catches also the case that the choice has a single aternative only
00352     if (a == 0) {
00353       GECODE_ME_CHECK(bin[c.item].eq(home, c.same[0]));
00354     } else {
00355       Iter::Values::Array same(c.same, c.n_same);
00356 
00357       GECODE_ME_CHECK(bin[c.item].minus_v(home, same));
00358 
00359       for (int i = c.item+1; (i<bin.size()) &&
00360                              (size[i] == size[c.item]); i++) {
00361         same.reset();
00362         GECODE_ME_CHECK(bin[i].minus_v(home, same));
00363       }
00364     }
00365     return ES_OK;
00366   }
00368   virtual void print(const Space&, const Gecode::Choice& _c,
00369                      unsigned int a,
00370                      std::ostream& o) const {
00371     const Choice& c = static_cast<const Choice&>(_c);
00372     if (a == 0) {
00373       o << "bin[" << c.item << "] = " << c.same[0];
00374     } else {
00375       o << "bin[" << c.item;
00376       for (int i = c.item+1; (i<bin.size()) &&
00377                              (size[i] == size[c.item]); i++)
00378         o << "," << i;
00379       o << "] != ";
00380       for (int i = 0; i<c.n_same-1; i++)
00381         o << c.same[i] << ",";
00382       o << c.same[c.n_same-1];
00383     }
00384   }
00385 };

00388 void cdbf(Home home, const IntVarArgs& l, const IntVarArgs& b,
00389           const IntArgs& s) {
00390   if (b.size() != s.size())
00391     throw Int::ArgumentSizeMismatch("cdbf");
00392   ViewArray<Int::IntView> load(home, l);
00393   ViewArray<Int::IntView> bin(home, b);
00394   IntSharedArray size(s);
00395   return CDBF::post(home, load, bin, size);
00396 }

00406 class BinPacking : public IntMinimizeScript {
00407 protected:
00409   const Spec spec;
00411   IntVarArray load;
00413   IntVarArray bin;
00415   IntVar bins;
00416 public:
00418   enum {
00419     MODEL_NAIVE, 
00420     MODEL_PACKING 
00421   };
00423   enum {
00424     BRANCH_NAIVE, 
00425     BRANCH_CDBF, 
00426   };
00428   BinPacking(const InstanceOptions& opt)
00429     : IntMinimizeScript(opt),
00430       spec(opt.instance()),
00431       load(*this, spec.upper(), 0, spec.capacity()),
00432       bin(*this, spec.items(), 0, spec.upper()-1),
00433       bins(*this, spec.lower(), spec.upper()) {
00434     // Number of items
00435     int n = bin.size();
00436     // Number of bins
00437     int m = load.size();
00438 
00439     // Size of all items
00440     int s = 0;
00441     for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00442       s += spec.size(i);
00443 
00444     // Array of sizes
00445     IntArgs sizes(n);
00446     for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00447       sizes[i] = spec.size(i);
00448 
00449     switch (opt.model()) {
00450     case MODEL_NAIVE:
00451       {
00452         // All loads must add up to all item sizes
00453         linear(*this, load, IRT_EQ, s);
00454 
00455         // Load must be equal to packed items
00456         BoolVarArgs _x(*this, n*m, 0, 1);
00457         Matrix<BoolVarArgs> x(_x, n, m);
00458 
00459         for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00460           channel(*this, x.col(i), bin[i]);
00461 
00462         for (int j=0; j<m; j++)
00463           linear(*this, sizes, x.row(j), IRT_EQ, load[j]);
00464       }
00465       break;
00466     case MODEL_PACKING:
00467       binpacking(*this, load, bin, sizes);
00468       break;
00469     }
00470 
00471     // Break symmetries
00472     for (int i=1; i<n; i++)
00473       if (spec.size(i-1) == spec.size(i))
00474         rel(*this, bin[i-1] <= bin[i]);
00475 
00476     // Pack items that require a bin for sure! (wlog)
00477     {
00478       int i = 0;
00479       // These items all need a bin due to their own size
00480       for (; (i < n) && (i < m) && (spec.size(i) * 2 > spec.capacity()); i++)
00481         rel(*this, bin[i] == i);
00482       // Check if the next item cannot fit to position i-1
00483       if ((i < n) && (i < m) && (i > 0) &&
00484           (spec.size(i-1) + spec.size(i) > spec.capacity()))
00485         rel(*this, bin[i] == i);
00486     }
00487 
00488     // All excess bins must be empty
00489     for (int j=spec.lower()+1; j <= spec.upper(); j++)
00490       rel(*this, (bins < j) == (load[j-1] == 0));
00491 
00492     branch(*this, bins, INT_VAL_MIN());
00493     switch (opt.branching()) {
00494     case BRANCH_NAIVE:
00495       branch(*this, bin, INT_VAR_NONE(), INT_VAL_MIN());
00496       break;
00497     case BRANCH_CDBF:
00498       cdbf(*this, load, bin, sizes);
00499       break;
00500     }
00501   }
00503   virtual IntVar cost(void) const {
00504     return bins;
00505   }
00507   BinPacking(bool share, BinPacking& s)
00508     : IntMinimizeScript(share,s), spec(s.spec) {
00509     load.update(*this, share, s.load);
00510     bin.update(*this, share, s.bin);
00511     bins.update(*this, share, s.bins);
00512   }
00514   virtual Space*
00515   copy(bool share) {
00516     return new BinPacking(share,*this);
00517   }
00519   virtual void
00520   print(std::ostream& os) const {
00521     int n = bin.size();
00522     int m = load.size();
00523     os << "Bins used: " << bins << " (from " << m << " bins)." << std::endl;
00524     for (int j=0; j<m; j++) {
00525       bool fst = true;
00526       os << "\t[" << j << "]={";
00527       for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00528         if (bin[i].assigned() && (bin[i].val() == j)) {
00529           if (fst) {
00530             fst = false;
00531           } else {
00532             os << ",";
00533           }
00534           os << i;
00535         }
00536       os << "} #" << load[j] << std::endl;
00537     }
00538     if (!bin.assigned()) {
00539       os << std::endl
00540          << "Unpacked items:" << std::endl;
00541       for (int i=0;i<n; i++)
00542         if (!bin[i].assigned())
00543           os << "\t[" << i << "] = " << bin[i] << std::endl;
00544     }
00545   }
00546 };

00551 int
00552 main(int argc, char* argv[]) {
00553   InstanceOptions opt("BinPacking");
00554   opt.model(BinPacking::MODEL_PACKING);
00555   opt.model(BinPacking::MODEL_NAIVE, "naive",
00556             "use naive model (decomposition)");
00557   opt.model(BinPacking::MODEL_PACKING, "packing",
00558             "use bin packing constraint");
00559   opt.branching(BinPacking::BRANCH_CDBF);
00560   opt.branching(BinPacking::BRANCH_NAIVE, "naive");
00561   opt.branching(BinPacking::BRANCH_CDBF, "cdbf");
00562   opt.instance(name[0]);
00563   opt.solutions(0);
00564   opt.parse(argc,argv);
00565   if (!Spec(opt.instance()).valid()) {
00566     std::cerr << "Error: unkown instance" << std::endl;
00567     return 1;
00568   }
00569   IntMinimizeScript::run<BinPacking,BAB,InstanceOptions>(opt);
00570   return 0;
00571 }
